  "notes": "STRUCTURAL ANCESTRY NODE. Kabyle-Atlas Berber is the immediate Glottolog subgroup above Kabyle (Glottolog kaby1244: Afro-Asiatic afro1255 > Berber berb1260 > Kabyle-Atlas Berber kaby1244 > Kabyle kaby1243). In the traditional dialectological classification this grouping falls within Northern Berber (a Zenati/Kabyle areal grouping); Glottolog — the authority used here — places Kabyle directly under this node, so it is modelled as such. Included so Kabyle's ancestry chain resolves without inventing phonology; the grapheme set is a minimal Berber-Latin placeholder inherited in spirit from ber. Spirantization is the shared Northern-Berber innovation.",
